commit_list.message:
Moves label text to props rather than children

Depends on FormidableLabs/victory-core/#10 We were previously assuming
that the children of custom labels contained accurate label information.
However, as discussed in FormidableLabs/victory-chart/#101 we are moving
to an api that supports making many clones of a single custom label
component based on an array of label values. That use case is clear in
not assuming that the children of the label 'factory' already know the
label text, it can't, we want to explicitly provide it.

So, I am proposing we eschew handling of injected components children.
Instead, we will provide our best guess at label text as a prop.

Match feedback in FormidableLabs/victory-core#10

commit_list.message:
Add support for providing label text as a prop

This is a fall back in the absence of children for the label. Custom label
components will receive label text through this prop when created by
victory components. Custom label components will not have their children
modified. Therefore, if we use VictoryLabel as a custom label component
as in:
https://github.com/FormidableLabs/victory-chart/blob/c72cfe78cb4a6091fa2a77e730bbce7ef78ba16e/demo/components/victory-scatter-demo.jsx#L101
then we need to allow for setting the label text through props.
